<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Backward2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Backward,</orth> adj., 1) being in the back: <cit><quote>his b. voice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 95</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) turned back: <cit><quote>with a b. look,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 59.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 59, 5</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>restem their b. course,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 38</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) unwilling, void of zeal: <cit><quote>perish the man whose mind is b. now!</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.72" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 72</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>